title: Bandelin Leads Comeback, UWS Beats CSS
text:
Bandelin Leads Comeback, UWS Beats CSS 
By Zach Schneider October 7, 2015 Updated Oct 7, 2015 at 9:50 PM CDT 
Superior, WI (NNCNOW.com) --- Esko, Minn. native Stephanie Bandelin finished with 27 kills on Wednesday night as the UW-Superior volleyball team rallied from a 2-0 deficit to beat St. Scholastica 3-2 in the first-ever conference clash between the two programs. 
Bandelin also added 10 digs in the winning effort, with Duluth, Minn. native Bailey Romans notching 17 kills and Ashlee Bayer getting 13. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
The match was the first-ever Upper Midwest Athletic Conference (UMAC) contest between UW-Superior and St. Scholastica, with the former currently going through its first year as part of the league. 
St. Scholastica, which saw a two-set lead slip away against its Twin Ports rival, was led by the 19 kills of Kortney Morrin. 
The two teams met earlier this season in a non-conference clash, which the Saints won 3-1, so the regular season series ends with one win apiece.
